1
00:00:12,387 --> 00:00:14,348
(SEAGULLS CAWING)

2
00:00:27,694 --> 00:00:29,780
(FIRE CRACKLING)

3
00:00:36,328 --> 00:00:37,829
(BORS SIGHS)

4
00:00:38,830 --> 00:00:40,207
How many days have I been here?

5
00:00:41,750 --> 00:00:44,044
-About three hours.
-(SOFTLY) Three hours?

6
00:00:44,127 --> 00:00:45,671
-Well, nearly.
-Maybe Clara's right.

7
00:00:46,463 --> 00:00:51,051
She keeps telling me I've got
attention deficit, uh...

8
00:00:52,553 --> 00:00:53,887
It's... It's something or other.

9
00:00:55,430 --> 00:00:57,266
-What is your journey?
-(EXHALES)

10
00:00:57,724 --> 00:00:59,101
Oh, you can't come with me, Bors.

11
00:00:59,184 --> 00:01:01,770
I pledged to your service
ever since you saved my life.

12
00:01:01,853 --> 00:01:04,106
I didn't save your life.
You had a splinter.

13
00:01:04,773 --> 00:01:08,527
Where is it you go?
Why must you meditate first?

14
00:01:10,571 --> 00:01:12,155
Someone I know is very sick.

15
00:01:13,365 --> 00:01:14,866
He'll want to see me before...

16
00:01:16,660 --> 00:01:18,078
While there's still time.

17
00:01:18,704 --> 00:01:19,871
An old friend?

18
00:01:20,163 --> 00:01:21,164
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

19
00:01:23,250 --> 00:01:24,918
Someone I've known a very long time.

20
00:01:25,877 --> 00:01:27,921
If there is danger,
let me ride at your side.

21
00:01:28,005 --> 00:01:29,715
You can't help me.

22
00:01:30,591 --> 00:01:31,883
Not where I'm going.

23
00:01:32,593 --> 00:01:34,136
I have to get myself ready.

24
00:01:35,053 --> 00:01:36,430
I have to be alone.

25
00:01:37,723 --> 00:01:38,890
I have to think.

26
00:01:39,558 --> 00:01:41,101
No more distractions.

27
00:01:41,977 --> 00:01:43,395
As you wish, Sir Doctor.

28
00:01:46,064 --> 00:01:47,566
Ugh! Hang on a minute.

29
00:01:49,151 --> 00:01:50,152
The water.

30
00:01:50,235 --> 00:01:51,820
-The water, sir?
-I don't like it.

31
00:01:51,903 --> 00:01:54,072
I can't meditate properly
without decent water.

32
00:01:58,493 --> 00:02:01,580
We're going to dig a well
right on, uh...

33
00:02:02,164 --> 00:02:04,708
This spot. Very excellent water.

34
00:02:04,791 --> 00:02:05,792
Right here.

35
00:02:05,876 --> 00:02:07,502
-How do you know?
-(SCOFFS)

36
00:02:07,586 --> 00:02:08,962
I'm very good at water.

37
00:02:12,174 --> 00:02:14,009
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

38
00:02:14,092 --> 00:02:16,261
This is definitely a good spot
for water.

39
00:02:16,720 --> 00:02:20,015
But this is the 12th place
you've made us dig.

40
00:02:20,098 --> 00:02:22,476
-Well, 12 is my lucky number.
-(CROWD GROANS)

41
00:02:25,854 --> 00:02:27,689
Here! No, here.

42
00:02:27,773 --> 00:02:28,857
Look at this grass.

43
00:02:28,940 --> 00:02:30,359
This is watery grass.

44
00:02:30,442 --> 00:02:31,526
Follow the squelching.

45
00:02:34,571 --> 00:02:36,114
(ROPE CREAKING)

46
00:02:38,617 --> 00:02:41,036
Well, you've all the water you need now

47
00:02:41,119 --> 00:02:43,246
and it's the finest in the land.

48
00:02:43,330 --> 00:02:45,040
Your meditation can begin.

49
00:02:45,123 --> 00:02:46,625
Yes, I suppose it can.

50
00:02:47,959 --> 00:02:49,378
-Except...
-Sir?

51
00:02:49,461 --> 00:02:50,962
Do you know what this well really needs?

52
00:02:51,046 --> 00:02:53,131
-Nothing! It's perfect.
-A visitor's center.

53
00:02:53,298 --> 00:02:54,925
-(SIGHS)
-(RATTLING)

54
00:02:55,467 --> 00:02:56,927
(SPLASHING)

55
00:02:58,512 --> 00:02:59,971
(MUMBLING)

56
00:03:01,932 --> 00:03:02,933
(BLOWING SHARPLY)

57
00:03:04,393 --> 00:03:07,688
I don't want to secrete onto your plan
for the throne room extension,

58
00:03:07,771 --> 00:03:10,774
but we're not quite sure
what you mean by "a sunroof.”

59
00:03:10,857 --> 00:03:13,151
-Look at this coin, you see it?
-I see it.

60
00:03:15,821 --> 00:03:17,364
-Where is it now?
-There.

61
00:03:18,615 --> 00:03:20,742
-No, it isn't.
-Yes, it is. I saw it.

62
00:03:21,076 --> 00:03:22,285
Are you sure?

63
00:03:23,662 --> 00:03:25,247
I'm really a very good magician.

64
00:03:25,497 --> 00:03:26,790
What is it you dread?

65
00:03:28,208 --> 00:03:29,584
Why would I dread anything?

66
00:03:29,668 --> 00:03:32,170
You're always making jokes.
You never sit still.

67
00:03:32,587 --> 00:03:34,464
You're like a man in fear
of days to come.

68
00:03:36,425 --> 00:03:38,844
-I thought you were an idiot.
-I know, I thought that, too.

69
00:03:40,721 --> 00:03:41,722
Good.

70
00:03:42,264 --> 00:03:44,307
I was worried I would have to
break it to you.

71
00:03:50,480 --> 00:03:52,107
(WIND HOWLING OUTSIDE)

72
00:03:52,607 --> 00:03:53,692
Are you sure?

73
00:03:54,401 --> 00:03:55,569
I've been avoiding it.

74
00:03:57,112 --> 00:03:58,321
One last night.

75
00:03:58,780 --> 00:03:59,948
Then I have to go.

76
00:04:00,031 --> 00:04:02,492
-You wish to be alone?
-I have to prepare myself.

77
00:04:02,576 --> 00:04:03,869
Why? You've never explained.

78
00:04:04,453 --> 00:04:06,788
I did something wrong.
I let somebody down

79
00:04:06,872 --> 00:04:08,623
when I should've been brave enough,

80
00:04:08,707 --> 00:04:10,959
strong enough, to do better.

81
00:04:11,251 --> 00:04:12,669
Tomorrow, I pay the price.

82
00:04:13,336 --> 00:04:15,964
Tonight, I make myself ready.

83
00:04:18,884 --> 00:04:20,051
Goodbye, magician.

84
00:04:20,927 --> 00:04:22,387
You have widened my mind.

85
00:04:25,891 --> 00:04:28,059
You do realize you're still an idiot?

86
00:04:28,894 --> 00:04:30,103
Yeah. (CHUCKLES)

87
00:04:30,187 --> 00:04:31,229
Good.

88
00:04:34,107 --> 00:04:35,484
I have to be quiet now.

89
00:04:36,485 --> 00:04:37,819
Quiet as the grave.

90
00:04:38,236 --> 00:04:40,155
I do not believe
you are capable of silence.

91
00:04:40,238 --> 00:04:41,239
Oh?

92
00:04:42,032 --> 00:04:43,950
(STUTTERING) Oh, well we'll see
about that, shall we?

93
00:04:44,034 --> 00:04:45,368
We shall, Sir Doctor.

94
00:04:46,661 --> 00:04:48,955
No more distractions. Total focus.

95
00:04:49,414 --> 00:04:50,707
No more distractions.

96
00:04:52,334 --> 00:04:53,418
(YELLING) Bors!

97
00:04:56,296 --> 00:04:58,173
-Are you any good with a broadsword?
-Yes.

98
00:04:58,256 --> 00:04:59,257
(CLINKING)

99
00:04:59,341 --> 00:05:02,093
-Fancy a friendly?
-Enough, magician!

100
00:05:02,928 --> 00:05:05,680
I do not believe that you will meditate.
It is not in your nature.

101
00:05:05,764 --> 00:05:08,642
If this is to be your last night here,
then we shall celebrate.

102
00:05:09,351 --> 00:05:10,602
There shall be revelries.

103
00:05:11,978 --> 00:05:13,146
-But first...
-First?

104
00:05:13,563 --> 00:05:14,773
Tell me your story.

105
00:05:15,357 --> 00:05:16,483
Tell me how you came to this place

106
00:05:16,566 --> 00:05:19,069
and why now,
you're compelled to leave it.

107
00:05:19,152 --> 00:05:20,487
(WIND CONTINUES HOWLING OUTSIDE)

108
00:05:21,404 --> 00:05:23,782
I will not depart this room
until you do so.

109
00:05:29,162 --> 00:05:31,873
-I suppose I do owe you.
-I've served you loyally, Sir Doctor.

110
00:05:31,957 --> 00:05:33,166
Yes.

111
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:36,086
Yes, you have.

112
00:05:36,962 --> 00:05:38,255
Then begin your tale.

113
00:05:40,465 --> 00:05:42,175
(SIGHS) Well.

114
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:47,013
A little while ago,

115
00:05:47,889 --> 00:05:49,474
a very long way from here,

116
00:05:50,851 --> 00:05:52,477
I was looking for a bookshop.

117
00:05:55,313 --> 00:05:56,314
Instead,

118
00:05:58,108 --> 00:05:59,651
I found a battlefield.

119
00:06:01,361 --> 00:06:02,696
Story of my life.

120
00:06:08,910 --> 00:06:10,871
I've seen many battlefields.

121
00:06:10,954 --> 00:06:12,622
(GUNFIRE IN BACKGROUND)

122
00:06:12,706 --> 00:06:14,374
But this one will be different.

123
00:06:16,293 --> 00:06:17,335
This one...

124
00:06:17,419 --> 00:06:18,503
(MAN YELLING)

125
00:06:18,587 --> 00:06:20,005
Will be my last.

126
00:06:20,088 --> 00:06:21,965
(RAPID GUNFIRE)

